n from Flask might not serialize correctly. The endpoint should take the target_url parameter and apply the regex pattern to determine if it matches either www or beta subdomain.\n\nFor the pattern itself, I need to clarify whether the trailing slash is required or just indicates the start of a path. The regex `^(www|beta)\\.example\\.com/` would only match if the slash is present, but the requirement might mean the pattern should match the domain with or without additional path components following it.\n\nI'll interpret this as: the URL must start with either `www.example.com/` or `beta.example.com/`, so the pattern needs that slash to be present. This way, `www.example.com/path` would match, but `www.example.com` alone would not.\n\nThe Flask endpoint takes the `target_url` query parameter, applies the regex pattern `^(www|beta)\\.example\\.com/` to check if it starts with the correct domain and subdomain, then returns the boolean result as JSON.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4656,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4656},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cfd8519-e9af-4c9d-bff8-073f06f94a49","uuid":"050d1de0-52d3-4904-a1ce-73132493acc9","request_id":"req_011CbdMy34nqapB6gmykLe9L"}
